getWavelet

public Wavelet getWavelet(java.lang.String waveId,
                          java.lang.String waveletId)
Description copied from interface: RobotMessageBundle
Creates a reference wavelet for the given wave id and wavelet id. If the wavelet is not currently on the robot, the metadata may not be complete. Still the wavelet may be used to perform operations where this metadata is not needed. If the wavelet does not exist in the Wave system, no operations will be performed. A new wavelet must be created with the createWavelet() method.

Specified by:
getWavelet in interface RobotMessageBundle
Parameters:
waveId - the wave id of the wavelet
waveletId - the wavelet id of the wavelet
Returns:
a wavelet referred to by the wave id / wavelet id combination.

getBlip

public Blip getBlip(java.lang.String waveId,
                    java.lang.String waveletId,
                    java.lang.String blipId)
Description copied from interface: RobotMessageBundle
Creates a reference blip for the given wave id, wavelet id and blip id. If the blip is not currently on the robot, the metadata may not be complete. Still the blip may be used to perform operations where this metadata is not needed. If the blip does not exist in the Wave system, no operations will be performed. A new blip must be created with the appendBlip(), createChild(), or insertInlineBlip() methods.

Specified by:
getBlip in interface RobotMessageBundle
Parameters:
waveId - the wave id of the wavelet
waveletId - the wavelet id of the wavelet
blipId - the blip id of the blip
Returns:
a blip referred to by the wave id / wavelet id / blip id triple.
